    <has_dmc>No</has_dmc>
  </oversight_info>
  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      The primary objective was to study the clinical benefit with dalteparin sodium in
      thromboprophylaxis in primary care medical subjects. The secondary objective was a
      pharmacoeconomic evaluation of hromboprophylaxis with dalteparin sodium in primary care
      medical subjects.
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
  <detailed_description>
    <textblock>
      The study was prematurely terminated on December 9, 2003. The reason for the early
      termination was not related to a safety or efficacy issue. It was related to the difficulty
      in recruiting patients.
    </textblock>
  </detailed_description>
